data.text:
CAREER HONORS

- 2024 Senior Bowl

- 2023 First-Team All-Big 12

- 2023 Second-Team Associated Press All-Big 12

- 2023 Honorable Mention Big 12 Offensive Player of the Year

- 2023 First-Team Academic All-Big 12

- 2023 Big 12 Offensive Player of the Week, vs. Baylor

- 2023 Senior Bowl Offensive Player of the Week, vs. Baylor

- 2023 East-West Shrine Bowl Texas Star of the Week, vs. Baylor

- 2023 Earl Campbell Tyler Rose Award Honorable Mention Player of the Week, vs. Baylor

- 2022 Honorable-Mention All-Big 12

- 2022 First-Team Academic All-Big 12

- 2021 First-Team Academic All-Big 12

- 2020 Second-Team Academic All-Big 12

2023 | SENIOR

Team Captain ... started all 12 games ... his team-best 47 receptions ranked fourth nationally for Power Five tight ends ... also topped TCU with eight touchdown catches to tie for the national lead among players at his position ... it was also the most by a Horned Frog since Jalen Reagor had nine in 2018 ... set a career-high in receptions in each of the final three games of the season ... his 178 yards receiving in a 42-17 win over Baylor broke TCU and Big 12 records for a tight end and were the most nationally by a player at that position for the year ... totaled seven catches, including touchdowns of 81 and 28 yards, in the rout of the Bears ... the 81-yard score was the longest reception of his career ... closed the season with a personal-best eight catches and two touchdowns at Oklahoma ... totaled six receptions for 65 yards versus Texas ... had first-half scoring receptions of 9 and 2 yards as part of five catches in a 34-17 win over SMU ... also recorded five receptions, including a 21-yard touchdown, versus Colorado ... his 7-yard scoring grab gave TCU a 24-0 first-half lead en route to a 44-11 victory against BYU ... totaled four receptions in the game ... recorded at least one catch in all 12 contests with multiple receptions in 10 games.

2022 | SENIOR

Placed fifth on TCU with a career-best 24 receptions, surpassing his career total (19) entering the season after three years at Texas ... tied for fourth on the team with four touchdown catches ... his 10-yard scoring reception from Max Duggan with 1:57 to play tied the Oklahoma State game at 30-30, as TCU went on to rally from a 17-point deficit for a 43-40 double-overtime win ... caught the game-tying 2-point pass from Duggan with 1:51 remaining to cap TCU's 11-point fourth quarter comeback in the Big 12 Championship Game against Kansas State ... the top-two receiving games of his career both came against K-State ... totaled a career-high five receptions for 74 yards, including a 4-yard touchdown, in the 38-28 regular-season win before recording four catches for 28 yards in the Big 12 title game ... his first touchdown as a Horned Frog was on a 6-yard catch against Tarleton ... had two receptions for 13 yards in his TCU debut in the season opening 38-13 win at Colorado ... had an 8-yard touchdown catch in the 42-34 win at SMU ... caught a 6-yard pass in the College Football Playoff Semifinal win over Michigan.

2021 | JUNIOR (TEXAS)

Played in 11 games with eight starts ... totaled nine receptions for 67 yards and two touchdowns ... had a season-best three catches for 26 yards and a touchdown against Rice ... the scoring grab versus the Owls came on a season long 20-yard catch ... had a 2-yard touchdown on his lone reception against Oklahoma ... recorded two catches versus Baylor and Kansas State.

2020 | SOPHOMORE (TEXAS)

Saw action in all nine regular-season games with starts against Texas Tech and Baylor ... caught nine passes for 166 yards and one touchdown ... recorded two catches for 63 yards, including a career long 52-yard reception, versus TCU ... had two receptions for 14 yards against Oklahoma ... caught two passes for 70 yards, including a 47-yard catch, versus Baylor ... had a 7-yard touchdown catch against No. 13 Iowa State ... did not play in the Alamo Bowl due to injury.

2019 | FRESHMAN (TEXAS)

Played in 12 games with two starts ... started against No. 13 Baylor and Texas Tech ... made his collegiate debut in the Louisiana Tech game ... had his first career start at No. 13 Baylor ... his first career reception went for 15 yards in the regular-season finale versus Texas Tech.
